Beijing municipality has applied to
the securities regulator to package five public rental projects
as real estate investment trusts, Sina.com  reported  today,
citing an unidentified city housing bureau official.  The proposed REITs will include 2,000 to 3,000 social
housing units, and is being formed in partnership with UBS AGâ€™s
Chinese joint venture UBS SDIC, the news website reported. The
pilot project is aimed at solving the long-term financing needs
of social housing, Sina said.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
